
Just flask hello world in docker with prometheus monitoring and grafana graphs.

== Dependencies ==
1. If you are going to run in docker:
 - make
 - docker
 - docker-compose
2. If you are going to deploy in kubernetes:
 - make
 - minikube (tested)
  or
 - kubectl with access to running cluster (untested)


== How to use ==
# In console execute
git clone https://github.com/q53/hello-world
cd hello-world
make
# follow the help message


